itemDescription.value: (1954-), Wife of Mark Norman Kemp-Gee; daughter of 10th Viscount Cobham
British author of non-fiction books for children and adults
British steeplechase, middle-distance and long-distance runner
British teacher and amateur wildlife sound recordist

English businessman who bought and established the fledgling Perrier brand of sparkling mineral water in France, designed its distinctive bulbous green bottle, and made it a huge success in the British Empire.
